21 SECTION 1. Arkansas Code Title 14, Chapter 116, Subchapter 1, is
22 amended to add an additional section to read as follows:
23 14-116-108. Election for fluoridation of water — Definition.
24 (a) Customers of a public water system shall have the option to hold
25 an election of the qualified electors of the public water system to determine
26 whether or not the public water system shall fluoridate the water.
27 (b)(1) An election under this section may be called by:
28 (A) Majority vote of the board of directors of the public
29 water system;
30 (B) A petition signed by no less than ten percent (10%) of
31 the qualified electors in the public water system;
32 (C) Majority vote of the board of directors or city
33 council of a city supplied by the public water system; or
34 (D) Majority vote of the quorum court of a county supplied
35 by the public water system.
36 (2)(A) Except as provided under subdivision (b)(2)(B) of this
